  "headline_findings": [
    "Structural validity 96.4% exceeds 90% target (single-error mode resolves v1 collateral damage).",
    "ToM cognitive gradient is empirically visible: GEMBA detection drops from 79% (L0) to 29% (L1) and 41% (L3).",
    "COMET score drop is roughly half at L3 (0.034) vs L0/L1 (0.072-0.075) — discourse errors sit below the reference-based metric's resolution.",
    "Severity labels are physically meaningful: COMET drop scales monotonically (minor 0.046 < major 0.065 < critical 0.081).",
    "Full pipeline beats B1 single-step by +31 pp on structural validity with equal error counts; B0 and B2 produce 0% categorisable items.",
    "GEMBA over-flags clean items (66% false positives) — automated QE is a coarse filter, not a pedagogical authority."
  ],
  "limitations": [
    "Three corpora instead of four (UNPC unavailable; EurLex replaces EUbookshop).",
    "EurLex lacks document IDs; L3 adjacent-pair segments are sourced from Europarl and DGT-TM only.",
    "GEMBA false-positive rate on clean items is high (66%) and inherent to LLM-as-a-judge.",
    "wmt22-comet-da used in place of xCOMET-XL (not supported by comet v2.2.7).",
    "Track B QE metrics (GEMBA, COMET) not yet computed on the 60 ablation items.",
    "Track C results (three-way agreement, explanation quality) pending annotator availability."
  ],
